net.vivialconnect.model.message

Class BulkMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.vivialconnect.model.VivialConnectResource
      • net.vivialconnect.model.message.BulkMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class BulkMessage
extends VivialConnectResource
    Bulk requests allow you to enqueue a large number of messages using only a few requests. A single local phone number can only send one message per second. To achieve greater throughput, use a Toll Free number or a Short Code with bulk send requests.

    For more info, visit Bulk Message

      • getFromNumber

        public String getFromNumber()
        For inbound messages, the external phone number that sent the text message. Uses E.164 format (+country code +phone number). For US, the format will be +1xxxyyyzzzz. For outbound messages, the associated phone number in your account that sent the text message.
        Returns:
        from number value

      • getToNumbers

        public List<String> getToNumbers()
        List of destination phone numbers for the text message in E.164 format: +1xxxyyyzzzz. Maximum list size is 100 numbers. Duplicates will be discarded.
        Returns:
        list of destination numbers
